  - question: I'm a Christian and I keep failing at this. Why can't I just stop?
    answer: >-
      Because willpower was never designed to carry this alone, and shame is
      gasoline, not brakes. White-knuckle purity cycles — sin, confess, swear
      off, repeat — keep men stuck for decades. Real change involves grace,
      honesty with other men, and dealing with what the habit is actually
      medicating. That's the work we do.
